Trade Request automation flows","description":"1. **Task creation**: After-save. Creates up to 5 tasks: Account Closing (2 biz days), FSA Journal, Follow-Up Form, Orion Fee Exclusion (5 biz days), Distribution Processing. Each triggered by corresponding checkbox/date field.\n2. **FPC notification**: After-save. Convert Chatter FPC notification (FA → PrimaryOwner → ReferredByContact traversal) to TRPG pattern.\n\nNote: NAS has 7+ existing flows. New flows must coexist.","url":"https://f2strategy.atlassian.net/browse/CET-114","status":"To Do","priority":"Medium","inCurrentCycle":false,"project":"Cetera","projectDescription":"","parent":{"id":"CET-110","title":"Case / TRPG Work Desk Alignment","description":""},"updatedAt":"2026-04-13T10:49:08.786-0500","assignee":{"email":"mac.nosek@f2strategy.com","name":"Mac Nosek"},"comments":[]},{"workspace":"F2","id":"CET-4","title":"Configure the custom package that drives the integration to Advice Works (Hold off on Creating until First Full Sandbox is set up)","description":"* Install into Sandbox _(Add installation to deployment process spreadsheet)_\n\n    * Connor was already working on installing this package into the Sandboxes\n    \n* Set up any necessary field mappings and configuration\n\n    * _See attached spreadsheet_\n    \n* Add “Send to Adviceworks” button to the Person Account Lightning Pages \n\n    * _Person Account Page Layout_\n    * _TRPG Client Lightning Page_\n    \n\n![](blob:https://media.staging.atl-paas.net/?type=file&localId=303d7133a5c9&id=881fb3b9-d628-4c87-bd69-dad25885ba75&&collection=&height=null&occurrenceKey=null&width=null&__contextId=null&__displayType=null&__external=false&__fileMimeType=null&__fileName=null&__fileSize=null&__mediaTraceId=null&url=null)Configuration guides:  \n  \n\n‌\n\nNotes from Odie on configuration:  \n\nHi guys, here'\''s the documentation we got from Chris when setting up this tool. A couple caveats I can'\''t remember if I'\''ve mentioned before about our pain points...\n\n1. We had a lot of back and forth testing to ensure no errors in the data being passed to AW. Picklist values and such aligning. Error handling isn'\''t great, and it required some help from the AW side to understand what was causing the errors. I'\''m hoping if we largely use values I provided, you won'\''t have to go through that trial and error exercise. I do not have AW access (the old PO did), but that will be required to see what comes through.\n\n2. Once the connection was established, we completed a data migration to AW for all existing clients. The migration was completed, but we have encountered problems when using the tool to update existing client as something in the data doesn'\''t match up with what is expected and is throwing the error. This is a problem we haven'\''t had much help in troubleshooting and is still an issue 6 months later. This is something we will have to be mindful of for the best experience for advisors.\n\n","url":"https://f2strategy.atlassian.net/browse/CET-4","status":"In Progress","priority":"Medium","inCurrentCycle":false,"project":"Cetera","projectDescription":"","parent":{"id":"CET-8","title":"Client Suitability Tracking","description":""},"updatedAt":"2026-04-13T10:48:25.275-0500","assignee":{"email":"mac.nosek@f2strategy.com","name":"Mac Nosek"},"comments":[]},{"workspace":"F2","id":"LNW-192","title":"Part 4: Visibility Enhancements POC - UI and UX Enablement","description":"Parent story for the UI glue layer: activity launcher card, entity selection panel with polished UX, and standard quick action overrides.\n\n**Scope:**\n\n* activityLauncherConfig__mdt Custom Metadata Type\n* activityLauncher LWC (compact quick-action card)\n* entitySelectionPanel LWC (UX wrapper around hierarchyEntityPicker)\n* Standard Quick Action Overrides (New Task, Event, Case routing)\n\n**Dependencies:** Requires Epic 1 (meetingNoteComposer), Epic 2 (aggregated timeline), and Epic 3 (familyRecordCreator, hierarchyEntityPicker) to be functional.","url":"https://f2strategy.atlassian.net/browse/LNW-192","status":"Review","priority":"Medium","inCurrentCycle":false,"project":"LNW","projectDescription":"","parent":{"id":"LNW-112","title":"Client Architecture","description":""},"updatedAt":"2026-04-06T08:04:25.758-0500","assignee":{"email":"mac.nosek@f2strategy.com","name":"Mac Nosek"},"comments":[]},{"workspace":"F2","id":"LNW-191","title":"Part 3: Visibility Enhancements POC -  Family Level Creation and Assignment","description":"Parent story that tracks all work for creating records at any hierarchy level and linking them to multiple entities.\n\n**Scope:**\n\n* Extend Meeting_Relation__c for Tasks & Events\n* FamilyRelationshipService (hierarchy resolution)\n* EntityRelationshipService (junction record CRUD)\n* FamilyRecordCreatorController (Apex controller)\n* hierarchyEntityPicker LWC (shared sub-component)\n* familyRecordCreator LWC (context-aware record creation)\n\n**Dependencies:** Requires Epic 1 (Meeting_Relation__c object and MeetingNoteService) to be completed first.","url":"https://f2strategy.atlassian.net/browse/LNW-191","status":"Review","priority":"Medium","inCurrentCycle":false,"project":"LNW","projectDescription":"","parent":{"id":"LNW-112","title":"Client Architecture","description":""},"updatedAt":"2026-04-06T08:04:24.274-0500","assignee":{"email":"mac.nosek@f2strategy.com","name":"Mac Nosek"},"comments":[]},{"workspace":"F2","id":"LNW-190","title":"Part 2: Visibility Enhancements POC - Aggregated Visibility","description":"Users currently have no way to see all activity across a Family in one place — they have to click into each Household, Institution, and Person Account separately. Epic 2 solves this by aggregating Tasks, Events, Cases, and Meeting Notes from all related entities onto a single Family-level timeline component (familyAggregatedTimeline).\n\n**Key Components:**\n\n* Apex: FamilyRelationshipService (shared with Epic 3 — see MSS-74)\n* Apex: AggregatedTimelineItem wrapper/DTO\n* Apex: FamilyActivityAggregationController\n* LWC: familyAggregatedTimeline (shell, rendering, filters, pagination)\n\n**Dependencies:**\n\n* FamilyRelationshipService is shared with Epic 3 (Story 3.2 / MSS-74). The account metadata resolution method needed for origin pill rendering has been added as a subtask under MSS-74.\n* Meeting Note ↔ Activity linking (Epic 1) for meetingNoteId population on timeline items\n\n","url":"https://f2strategy.atlassian.net/browse/LNW-190","status":"Review","priority":"Medium","inCurrentCycle":false,"project":"LNW","projectDescription":"","parent":{"id":"LNW-112","title":"Client Architecture","description":""},"updatedAt":"2026-04-06T08:04:22.860-0500","assignee":{"email":"mac.nosek@f2strategy.com","name":"Mac Nosek"},"comments":[]},{"workspace":"F2","id":"LNW-189","title":"Part 1: Visibility Enhancements POC - Meeting Note Additional Functionality","description":"Parent story that tracks all work for unifying Meeting Note creation with Activity linking, attendee management, and multi-entity relations.\n\n**Scope:**\n\n* Meeting_Relation__c junction object (data model)\n* Meeting Note ↔ Activity bidirectional linking (shadow Activities)\n* MeetingNoteService (Apex service layer)\n* MeetingNoteTrigger & Handler (trigger framework)\n* MeetingNoteComposerController (Apex controller)\n* meetingNoteComposer LWC (3 sections: Activity Type/Fields, Attendee Manager, Relations & Save)\n\n","url":"https://f2strategy.atlassian.net/browse/LNW-189","status":"Review","priority":"Medium","inCurrentCycle":false,"project":"LNW","projectDescription":"","parent":{"id":"LNW-112","title":"Client Architecture","description":""},"updatedAt":"2026-04-06T08:04:19.971-0500","assignee":{"email":"mac.nosek@f2strategy.com","name":"Mac Nosek"},"comments":[]}]'

